  node_paths edge_paths
  &lt;list&gt;     &lt;list&gt;    
1 &lt;int [68]&gt; &lt;int [67]&gt;
2 &lt;int [77]&gt; &lt;int [76]&gt;
3 &lt;int [56]&gt; &lt;int [55]&gt;
4 &lt;int [86]&gt; &lt;int [85]&gt;
5 &lt;int [56]&gt; &lt;int [55]&gt;
6 &lt;int [25]&gt; &lt;int [24]&gt;
7 &lt;int [30]&gt; &lt;int [29]&gt;


The result is a tibble with two list columns: node_paths (node indices) and edge_paths (edge indices). The edge_paths column is used in the next step to reconstruct the geometry of each path.

